<head>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" LINK="red" VLINK="black">
<title>Letter From Al -- December 9, 1996</title>
</head>
<body>
<p>
<center><img src="/nationalreview/images/topletr.gif" ALT="Letter From Al"></center>
<p>
<center><img src="/nationalreview/images/dear.gif"></center>
<P>
 <TABLE ALIGN=LEFT width=50%>
<TR>
<TH></TH>
<TD>                                                                





Tipper Gore, who gave no reason,<br>
Decided to celebrate this holiday season<br>
And replace the usual family Christmas letter --<br>
 
You know the one? With a Xeroxed header:<br>

``How the Gores spent the year that's waning''<br>

(You know how: they were all campaigning!) -- <br>

With a little rhyme, a Christmas corker,<br>

An idea borrowed from The New Yorker.<br>

<P>
Ninety-six brought the giddy knowledge<br>

That Al could say to the Electoral College<br>

When the tally is what the tally must be:<br>

``You like me!  You really, really like me!''<br>

Tipper, though thrilled with the second hitch,<br>

Doesn't want to come off like a rhymes-with-rich<br>

And is preparing to do a Liddy Dole,<br>

So, no, she'll have no ``formal role.''<br>

<P>
The kids are fine; each one is thriving.<br>

Karenna's job hunting, Sara is surviving<br>

The SATs and the Achievement Test,<br>
While on Saturdays Al Jr. does his best<br>

To show his savvy: with great aplomb<br>

He turns our Tipper into a Soccer Mom.<br>

Kristin is busy with her college choice,<br>

And has made it clear, in a tone of voice<br>

And with certain words that we can't go printin':<br>

She will not be roommates with Chelsea Clinton.<br>

<P>
But enough about us! This is supposed to be a letter of thanks<br>

To all of our friends at Indonesian banks.<br>

Warm the bourbon and stir the toddy<br>

For our old pal James Riady!<br>

Pop the cork and bang the gong:<br>

We've found Mr. Moneybags -- the Elusive Huang!<br>

So give out a yell, shout out a whoop<br>

For friends of the friends of the Lippo Group!<br>

And thank them for sharing their prosperity,<br>

But what exactly they do is a mystery to me.<br>

<P>
(Don't let our good cheer or flip tone offend ya -- <br>

Campaign Finance Reform is on our agenda.<br>

And stop pointing fingers; don't play the fool.<br>

Remember what happened to big fella Jewell?)<br>

<P>
Let's not stop there! Let the thanking continue<br>

Until the spirit of gratitude is surging in you.<br>

</tr>
</TABLE>
<P>
<TABLE>
<tr>
<TH></TH>
<td>

Poor Dick Morris and his upside-down life --<br>
 
Not as upside-down as his unfortunate wife,<br>

I mean the one in Connecticut, not the one in Texas --<br>
 
I think there's only two, I'll check Lexis/Nexis --<br>
 
He deserves our thanks. He was loyal and stout.<br>

(At least until his book comes out.)<br>

<P>
So thank you Dick! The ideological mickeys<br>

That you slipped Stephanopoulos and Ickes<br>

Did the trick. They were silent as stone,<br>

Until the polls closed in the Pacific Time Zone.<br>

It was your work, my friend, to you goes the credit,<br>

I'm only sorry that you'll never be feted.<br>

I remember the day you strode into the room,<br>

And broke through the mire and lifted the gloom,<br>

You scrawled a few words on the whiteboard beside you.<br>

``Listen up,'' you shouted. ``Let these five words guide you.''<br>

You tapped the whiteboard with the pen's plastic tip,<br>

And with five little words you rescued the ship:<br>

Newt's a wacko;<br>

Ban tobacco.<br>

<P>
(Keep in touch; don't be a stranger.<br>

I don't think my nomination's in any danger,<br>

But just in case -- it's a no-brainer -- <br>

I'm enclosing a hefty four-year retainer.)<br>

<P>
Thank you, Bob Reich, and a bouquet of flowers<br>

To the rest of the gang that's off to the showers.<br>

``Know when to say when'' is a saying we know.<br>

There's no shame in quitting -- are you listening, Miss Reno?<br>

<P>
So greetings to all, and to all a big thanks.<br>

We think of you as our '00 piggy banks.<br>

May '97 for all be finer and sweeter.<br>

(Just throw out all direct mail from the Minority Leader.)<br>

<P>
From the entire Gore clan, we wish you good cheer,<br>

During the holiday season and the coming New Year,<br>

Friends and family and presents fantastic,<br>

Under a Christmas tree made of recycled plastic.<br>

</TD>
